{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c123c754-d2e5-4aa7-9239-f86fa2e77861","content":"**`ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"`** — ✅ Yes, this is correct for .NET MAUI on .NET 10. You'll need the namespace:\n\n```xml\nxmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n```\n\n**`IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on a Grid** — ❌ This is **not** a standard .NET MAUI property. Your tutorial may be outdated or referencing a third-party library.\n\n### For a background image extending behind the notch:\n\nInstead, structure your page so the background sits outside the safe area while content respects it:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"...\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\">\n    <Grid>\n        <!-- Background fills entire screen including notch area -->\n        <Image Source=\"bg.png\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n\n        <!-- Content respects safe area via padding -->\n        <Grid Padding=\"{OnPlatform iOS='44,0,34,0'}\">\n            <!-- Your content here -->\n        </Grid>\n    </Grid>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nOr keep `UseSafeArea=\"True\"` on the page and set the background via the `Page.BackgroundImageSource` property, which naturally extends edge-to-edge.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a0f7532c-e714-4a63-93b2-c0d5bb0c58b0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI safe area handling on iOS, specifically about two attributes:\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` - for handling the iPhone notch\n2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` - on a Grid for a background image\n\nThey want to know if these are correct for .NET 10. Let me search for any relevant documentation or code in the current repository that might help answer this question.\n\nActually, looking at the environment, this is a repository with skill plugins. Let me check if there's any MAUI-related content here. But actually, I can answer this from my knowledge of .NET MAUI.\n\n\nFor the first attribute, `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` is indeed the correct way to handle safe areas on iOS in .NET MAUI, though you need to include the iOS-specific XML namespace. However, `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` isn't a standard .NET MAUI property—that's not how you'd typically ignore safe area constraints for individual elements in the framework. So `UseSafeArea` on iOS is the right approach for respecting safe area insets, but I'm uncertain whether `IgnoreSafeArea` is actually available as a standard property in .NET MAUI. The typical workaround for extending backgrounds behind the safe area while keeping content inset would involve a different strategy. Let me clarify what's actually supported in the current version. I'm realizing that `IgnoreSafeArea` isn't actually a standard property in .NET MAUI, so for background images that need to extend beyond the safe area while content respects it, the typical approach is to set the background directly on the page or use a specific layout structure rather than relying on that property.","outputTokens":1520,"requestId":"980B:1A0B9E:169D099:194B91B:6A052216"},"id":"1debfd65-c79f-41ba-b27b-ccfcb02e3e9e","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:15:30.888Z","parentId":"cb4b3442-8b46-4c76-817b-aaa4a977423a"}
